<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://score-theory.org/bac#"
     xml:base="http://score-theory.org/bac"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:core="http://score-theory.org/core#">

    <!-- SCORE-BAC: the Late Bronze Age collapse refinement of SCORE (the first historical /
         retrodictive child; sibling to POLARIS). A refinement P subset of S (see
         obsidian/SCORE/methodology/RefinementArchitecture.md): it imports the domain-independent
         core and SPECIALIZES core slots (Q2 of the decision procedure) - it adds no axiom that
         contradicts core. Conformance is consistency of core (+) bac under a DL reasoner.

         SOURCE-CRITICISM LAYER SCOPE DECISION (Phase C, development-plan item 1):
         RESOLVED to reading (i) - a SPECIALIZE of the inscription morphism. The construct adds
         domain axioms specializing core:Inscription (a preservation-filtered subtype whose B3
         product reached the 2026 researcher only by surviving a destruction / recovery process),
         which is new semantics over the morphism, not a pure data mapping. This makes SCORE-BAC
         the first peer to CONTRAST a morphism - DOEEvaluation gap #3 (the deep SELECTed
         machinery no peer has ever specialized). The competing reading (ii) - promoting the
         doc-slot DataBinding to an OWL abstraction for a single peer - is rejected as premature
         abstraction (RefinementArchitecture no-premature-abstraction rule).
         NUMERIC CONTENT IS Q4 BIND, NOT HERE: the survival function S = p_phys * p_exc * p_pub
         and the genre content-fidelity F live in code; this layer carries only the qualitative
         second-order (preservation) lossiness STRUCTURE.
         PRE-REGISTERED Q3 PROMOTION CANDIDATE: promote PreservationFilteredInscription to core
         the moment a SECOND sparse-evidence historical child needs the same construct (the ETHOS
         gap-surface-then-promote pattern). Until then it stays in this layer.
         Worked specification: obsidian/SCORE/emergence/applications/SCORE-BAC-SourceCriticism.md. -->
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac">
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core"/>
        <rdfs:comment>SCORE-BAC implementation ontology (Late Bronze Age collapse). SPECIALIZES core:Inscription (the source-criticism layer -- first morphism specialization in the family), core:HumanCommunity (the polity-as-cluster HOA analog; the retain pole, polity is an A-actor cluster, not a primitive SigmaActor), and core:MeasurementModel (the retrodictive differential-survival metric). The B1-as-distribution data posture and the numeric survival/fidelity functions are Q4 BIND (code), not ontology.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>Refinement conformance: core (+) bac verified consistent, no unsatisfiable classes (HermiT via owlready2). Reproduce: scripts/score_reason.py (auto-discovers score-*.owl).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>


    <!-- ============================ Object properties ============================ -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#survivedVia -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#survivedVia">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#PreservationFilteredInscription"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The destruction / abandonment circumstance through which the inscription's B3 product survived to be recovered. The second-order filter the layer formalizes: survival is itself a process, not a random sample of the B3 that existed in 1200 BCE.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#onCarrier -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#onCarrier">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#PreservationFilteredInscription"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The carrier material of the B1 mark that realizes (core:carriedBy) the surviving B3 product. Material co-determines survival with destruction mode (p_phys); the pairing is the load-bearing axis of S.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>


    <!-- ============================ The morphism SPECIALIZE ============================ -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#PreservationFilteredInscription -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#PreservationFilteredInscription">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Inscription"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#survivedVia"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#onCarrier"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label>Preservation-filtered inscription</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The source-criticism construct: a subtype of the core:Inscription morphism whose B3 product is subject to the second-order preservation filter (survival via a destruction mode, on a carrier material) before it reaches the researcher. THE first specialization of a morphism in the SCORE family (DOEEvaluation gap #3). Orthogonal to the referent typing (core:B1ReferentialInscription / core:B2ReferentialInscription): preservation is about survival of the mark, referent typing is about content -- a preservation-filtered inscription may be of either referent. The numeric survival likelihood S and genre fidelity F that turn this structure into a likelihood over B2 states are Q4 BIND (code), not modeled here -- DL cannot express the function. Pre-registered Q3 promotion candidate. See SCORE-BAC-SourceCriticism.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ============================ Destruction-mode axis ============================ -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode">
        <rdfs:comment>The circumstance of destruction / abandonment that conditions survival (p_phys depends on it). The four modes below are pairwise disjoint.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionByFire -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionByFire">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The confounded channel: a destruction fire BAKES clay archives into near-permanence, so survival probability is HIGHEST exactly where peaceful continuity FAILED. Corpus richness then reports mode-of-death, not administrative depth -- the central bias the layer exists to correct (Ugarit, Hattusa, Pylos).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#GradualAbandonment -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#GradualAbandonment">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Peaceful decline: unbaked clay slumps, organics decay, little survives in situ. The low-survival counterpart to destruction-by-fire -- a polity that declined quietly leaves a thin trace.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#DeliberateArchival -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#DeliberateArchival">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Intentional curation / storage: a non-destruction survival path, genre-selective (what a culture chose to keep), introducing a curation bias distinct from the fire channel.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#LootingReuse -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#LootingReuse">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionMode"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Looting / material reuse: a systematic LOSS channel, acute for metal (bronze recycled precisely when scarce in a collapse) -- non-random destruction biased against valuable carriers.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ============================ Carrier-material axis ============================ -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial">
        <rdfs:comment>The material of the B1 mark realizing the surviving B3 product (qualifies the core:carriedBy B1 mark). Co-determines p_phys with destruction mode. The five materials below are pairwise disjoint.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#FiredClay -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#FiredClay">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial"/>
        <rdfs:comment>High persistence CONDITIONAL on baking (destruction-by-fire); sun-dried clay slumps without it. The interaction with DestructionByFire is the model's central confound.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#Papyrus -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#Papyrus">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Persistence near zero except in arid undisturbed burial; the humid Nile Delta loses nearly all administrative papyrus, so Egypt's administrative B2 must be INFERRED, not read -- the Egypt adaptive-response variable under test.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#StoneMonument -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#StoneMonument">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Very high persistence but low information density and genre-locked to commemoration -- over-represents the legitimating B3, under-represents distributed administration (Medinet Habu, the Merneptah Stele).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#Metal -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#Metal">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Physically durable but under acute recycling pressure in a collapse (bronze scarcity) -- a systematic, non-random loss channel (see LootingReuse).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#OrganicMaterial -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#OrganicMaterial">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/bac#CarrierMaterial"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Wood, textile, leather: persistence near zero except waterlogged-anoxic or arid (the Uluburun cargo survives only because it sank) -- idiosyncratic survival, a reminder that S is mode-specific.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ============================ HOA-analog slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:HumanCommunity) ============================ -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#PolityCluster -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#PolityCluster">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#HumanCommunity"/>
        <rdfs:label>Polity cluster (omega-bounded)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>SCORE-BAC HOA analog: an emergent, coupling-opacity (omega)-bounded cluster of individual elite/administrative A-actor agents (low intra-cluster omega, high inter-cluster omega). The RETAIN pole of the coalesce/retain choice -- a polity is an A-actor cluster, NOT a primitive SigmaActor; individual constituent THSs are retained and polity aggregates computed on demand, so the differential-survival distribution is preserved. Derived by the same structural-equivalence machinery as POLARIS GeographicCommunity (see HOA.md, CollectiveManifold.md, ActorTypes.md).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ============================ Measurement-model slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:MeasurementModel) ============================ -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#DifferentialSurvivalModel -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#DifferentialSurvivalModel">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#MeasurementModel"/>
        <rdfs:label>Differential-survival retrodiction model</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>SCORE-BAC measurement model: a retrodictive metric over the known differential-survival outcome (full collapse -- Hatti, the Mycenaean palaces, Ugarit; transformation -- Cyprus; survival-with-diminishment -- Egypt). The role-level POLARIS-SEWI analog (fills core:MeasurementModel; not a core:SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator -- retrodictive over a known outcome, not a spectral trace processor) for a historical retrodiction target rather than a live early-warning index. Domain-specific refinement; no differential-survival metric belongs in core. See RetrodictionFramework.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ============================ Disjointness ============================ -->

    <rdf:Description>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AllDisjointClasses"/>
        <owl:members rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#DestructionByFire"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#GradualAbandonment"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#DeliberateArchival"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#LootingReuse"/>
        </owl:members>
    </rdf:Description>

    <rdf:Description>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AllDisjointClasses"/>
        <owl:members rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#FiredClay"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#Papyrus"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#StoneMonument"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#Metal"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#OrganicMaterial"/>
        </owl:members>
    </rdf:Description>


    <!-- ============================ Doctrinal-region + composition fillers ============================
         Q2 SPECIALIZE of the promoted core:DoctrinalRegion / core:doctrinallyComposesFrom
         (eighth-promotion slot, 2026-06-21). DISTINCTIVE: bac:PolityCorpus is the polity's INTENDED
         region (down-closed); the preservation filter (bac:PreservationFilteredInscription, the
         source-criticism layer) yields a SURVIVING subset that need not be down-closed — a surviving
         decree whose source record is lost. The source-criticism hazard, on the region structure.
         Lean formal/Formal/Score/Bac.lean (bacNetwork; the preservation-breaks-down-closure witness). -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#derivesFromRecord -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#derivesFromRecord">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#doctrinallyComposesFrom"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Documentary composition among B3 historical inscriptions: `y derivesFromRecord x` means decree / synthesis y is grounded in substrate x (an administrative record, a prior decree). The SCORE-BAC instance of core:doctrinallyComposesFrom.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/bac#PolityCorpus -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/bac#PolityCorpus">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#DoctrinalRegion"/>
        <rdfs:label>Polity corpus (intended)</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A bac:PolityCluster's INTENDED corpus: the graded down-set of the derivesFromRecord DAG the polity co-inscribed. The SCORE-BAC filler of core:DoctrinalRegion. Crucially, the *surviving* corpus is this region passed through the preservation filter (bac:PreservationFilteredInscription) and so need NOT be down-closed — a surviving decree whose source record is lost (the source-criticism hazard). Lean: formal/Formal/Score/Bac.lean (bacPolityCorpus, bacPolityCorpus_isRegion; the preservation-breaks-down-closure witness). See SCORE-BAC-SourceCriticism.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

</rdf:RDF>

<!-- Authored for SCORE-BAC development-plan item 1 (source-criticism layer). -->
